* USAGE =>
	netln -h
	netln -t bridge -n br0 -r 192.168.3.1 -p 24 -Y
	netln -t bridge -n br0 -m 00:11:22:33:44:55 -Y
	netln -t bridge -a DELETE -n br0 -Y
	netln -t veth -n veth0 -e veth1 -Y
	netln -t veth -n veth0 -e veth1 -m 00:11:22:33:44:55 -M 66:77:88:99:aa:bb -Y

  * ABOUT =>
	Script create or delete network interfaces.
	Use -t bridge or -t veth for interface type.
	Use -a ADD or -a DELETE for action.